result.execSummary:
The defendant Alicia L Beerbohm was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Cocaine/Coca [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(c).
  • Possession of Cocaine/Coca [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(c).
  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt: 3:31 pm case called. Defendant Alicia L Beerbohm in court with attorney William Michael Lennon.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement stated on the record which would amend counts 3 & 4 to Possession of Cocaine, as a party to the crime, contrary to 961.41(3g)(c).    Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Court accepts amendment of Counts 3 & 4 as requested by the State. Plea: No Contest to Counts 3, 4, & 5.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses and reads-in Counts 1 & 2. Statement by DA. Statement by Attorney Lennon. No statement by Defendant. Court sentences the defendant to: SWD and places the defendant on probation for a period of 2 years. CONDITIONS: CT 3 ONLY-75 days WCJ, with Huber. To begin service no later than December 1, 2015. Credit for 25 day served. Court does not object to transfer of jail sentence to another county. No EMD. CONDITIONS ON ALL COUNTS-No contact with co-defendant Jermaine Douglas.   The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Buy money to be reimbursed in the amount of $1150.00-joint & several. Terms of Agent. DNA sample. Appeal Rights Given.

Case Called @ 11:05 AM: Defendant Alicia L Beerbohm in court with attorney William Michael Lennon.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Preliminary Hearing and Time Limits discussed. Defendant wishes to waive preliminary hearing. Court questions defendant and accepts waiver of preliminary hearing.   Complaint describes facts establishing Probable Cause that she committed the alleged offenses.  Def BOT.  ARGN to proceed.  INFO Filed - Stated - Reading Waived.  NGP rec'd and entered as to all charges of INFO.  Atty Lennon argues as to modification of bond to Signature Bond.   The Court:  Declines to modify bond due to the offenses alleged and ties to the community.  Bond modification respectfully declined.  STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State.  Status conference scheduled for October 1, 2015 at 02:20 pm.
